<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President of Chile</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-19">August 19,
                                        1906</date></hi>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In the name of the people of the United States I offer tribute of sorrow
                            and sympathy to their afflicted brethren of Chile by reason of the awful
                            disaster that has befallen Valparaiso.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>